caption: Such a welcome addition to the neighborhood that already had a bunch of taco places that are all exactly the same. 1st the service was great, the decor is modern with lots of plants. 2nd the food was awesome, we had guac, tacos, the shrimp ceviche type appetizer, quesadilla and the fish of the day (we love that it comes with veggies rather then rice and beans). I had to give up my fish taco to one of the kids who couldn't wait for his 2nd one to come. Drinks are great too. Will definitely return.

Good Food, Good Service! Really pleasant owner working the bar! I enjoyed the Vegetarian entree with the green sauce - Verde. A tasty blend of greens in a smother in a puree. Yum! The lights stay bright which give a cantina feel more so than an atmospheric restaurant. Simple selection of healthy plants for decor!
I ate the food too fast to take pictures 😭 the octopus tostado is amazing and so are the tacos & burritos 🌯🌮
Delicious food and great staff!! Definitely will go back.

Excellent food and drinks. Service just as good. Homemade Guacamole is out of this world. As for the 1 star review from Mike, he gave 1 star because of the price. People like you should stay home and eat frozen dinners. The prices here aren't really high. I don't know what he's talking about.
Gourmet fresh Authentic Mexican food. Kind service. Solid twice a week take out.
A fav place for Cheap food. This place is absolutely one of my favorites. The staff was very friendly and attentive. Prices were average for the menu. I can see why they have so many reviews.
Mexicana Steak - Very good. The salad it was served with was very good too.

This is the strongest 5 star recommendation I could ever give. Listen to none of the 4 star reviews! The service was impeccable! Shout out to Jackson and Alex, the pastry chef, and everyone else who served us and who I, shamefully, did not get names from. The food was exquisite, interesting, and imaginative. There aren't enough words to describe the experience of eating what was prepared for my just-said-yes fiance and I. If you're looking for an experience for a special occasion or just because you can, look no further!
Food is good. Service is great. Love the team service atmosphere. Food is always got and fresh. Fast and good.

The restaurant staff was very warm and friendly. From my perspective, it seemed family-managed with a father & son present running the dining area. The prices for the dish were extremely fair being in Bayridge. In addition, the taste of the plates were very unexpected in a positive light with a slight kick to traditional Mexican recipes. Even the owner of the business was kind enough to take photos by the decoration with my wife to help promote his business being only a year in town.  My score still stands at 5 stars only to some suggestions to the owner: a recommendation to invest in light dimmers. At times I felt our table was extremely well lit however that didn't really bother me as a diner but it could damper the experience to perhaps a couple going for a romantic ambiance. A second recommendation is to have condiments available at the table. It was unusual that salt, pepper and additional napkins weren't present at each table. My final suggestion is to decorate the restaurant further - the establishment has SOOO much potential. The walls are massive and it appears to be built well so take advantage with more decoration or artwork. Other than that, for a business only a year in town (especially a crummy year at best) I cannot wait to visit once more!
The best fish tacos in the area! The staff is always very nice and friendly!
Ordered in from here and it was absolutely delicious. I had the vegetable burrito with a side of guac, and it was worth every penny.
Really good Guac. Nice design. Will be back when  indoor dining reopens
Excelent Mexican  Food
Excelent mexican Food

Got to meet the owner while waiting for my green and mole poblano enchiladas. Very nice chat with a man that’s making a humongous effort to keep this restaurant afloat. He started with 2020 and we all know what happened next and he’s still here. Great food we had. His high end Tequilas are also difficult to find even in good places in Mexico. This is very good food and whoever is expecting to find a cheap burrito better go to Taco Bell. Aleli surprised us with its delicious enchiladas. Coming back for sure. Felicidades!
Great food and modern space. Try the Octopus tostada.
Exceptional food, very nice staff, constantly excellent atmosphere. They charge affordable prices and the food quality is very good. I recommend this place.

AMAZING!!! Me and the family were in the neighborhood looking for a random place to eat and came across this gem. Everything was FRESHLY prepared and authentic Mexican food. I live in New Jersey and will definitely take the drive back to this wonderful establishment. We ordered the chips w/ guacamole, veggie burrito, rice and seafood, side of rice and beans.

At first from the outside of the building it looks like a takeout place. Don't judge a book by its cover! Amazing authentic Mexican food! We had the steak and chicken tacos, and the chicken enchilada with mole sauce. The best Mole we've eaten. Everything was so tasty and you can tell that it was cooked with love. The Margaritas were also excellent. Service was great. We will definitely be going back and bringing friends.😊
Amazing food, great quality and great service.
Very good food and service

BEST fish tacos I’ve ever had. Fried to perfection. Everything was so flavorful. Restaurant staff were friendly and funny. I will come back often for the fish tacos, chicken mole and octopus tostada.  Anyone that says it’s pricey are probably use to chipotle and Taco Bell. This place is NOT that! Aleli is comparable to authentic/upscale food you find in Mexico City.  Recommendation: could use better ambience lighting indoors and outdoors. Hire more staff, I saw a few people walk away because they were not acknowledged or seated right away. Understandable though! The waiters were so swamped.

Amazing fish tacos!!! Chicken mole was delicious!! The octopus tostada delicious as well!  The people that run the restaurant are the sweetest. I highly recommend and will definitely be coming back often.
Ordered take out and the food and guac was fresh and delicious. Ordered in the past and it still gets 5 ⭐️! Will order again.
I appreciate the flavors and preparations. Delish!
The food is delicious authentic Mexican food, admirable FAMILY service.  Muchísimas gracias!

I was introduced to this place by a friend of mine. Food is delicious. I think this is the best authentic Mexican food I’ve had in years. Sangrias are amazing. Service - they are so sweet and so polite. I enjoy going every time. I highly recommend this place to anyone.  Please try their pollo adobado and white sangria.  Delicious!!!!!5 ⭐️
Quite place for dinner or lunch. Great sangria and fish tacos!
Seriously some of the most amazing Mexican I’ve had in Bay Ridge!!! Always freshly prepared! Great people, Alex and Juan are awesome!!! ! A hidden gem for sure!!

We ordered dinner from Aleli this evening and I must say we were very pleased with food. The octopus appetizer was excellent and the chicken burritos were awesome!!! If your looking for clean, authentic Mexican food Aleli is your place! We will definitely be ordering from them again soon.
Easily the best Mexican food in NYC/BK and most hardworking team.
It was a nice dinner in this place. Thanks
The octopus tostada alone is worth a visit!  Delicious!

Aleli has the best fish tacos in Bay Ridge! This restaurant is worth trying and supporting. They have a backyard which they plan to open soon and it is wheelchair accessible (ramp in front and large bathroom). They just got their liquor license (as of July 1, 2020).

Let me start by saying I’m so glad they changed their menu. When they first opened, I didn’t think they would survive based on their menu, and the prices. Then coronavirus hit, and I thought they might not be back. When they re-opened, they had drastically changed their menu, for the better imho. I’ve had quite a few of their dishes, and just the other day I had their burrito, which is what prompted this review. It was one of the best burritos I’ve ever had! Their chicken mole poblano, their chicken adobado, their tacos (I’ve had all of them except the chorizo), guacamole are all excellent. I wish they included beans with the adobado dish in particular, but this is a small complaint. They are friendly and food is fresh and very tasty. Bay Ridge has a few Mexican restaurants and a Cali Mexican restaurant in Hobrah, but in my opinion, this is the best Mexican restaurant in Bay Ridge...by far. You owe it to yourself to try them out.
$13 for a Burrito and $11 for "Traditional Guacamole" ?!?! Are these people serious ? They obviously are because the restaurant is almost always empty.... Get lost.
Great high-end Mexican food and warm, wonderful staff!

Refined Mexican food. Not your typical fare.  Delicious, thoughtfully presented with great service.  Short rib and coconut flan were excellent.  If we could change anything, it would be to have warmer/lower lighting for a more romantic ambiance.  Otherwise a great experience!

Aleli. Quality. Careful choice of ingredients. And great spice combinations. And right across the street from me! So the cons: dessert menu only really has one item right now. I need more! But the coconut flan was rich dense and smooth. Good flavor and popped amaranth which is a treat. I got the spicy guacamole. Because guacamole, duh. They fry up the chips there. Perfect thickness and salt. Loved the guac. So many textures and flavor. A very nice blend. It's not very spicy either. Next was the memelita. This was a pleasant surprise. The shell here was made from scratch and grilled. It held up well to the vegetables and sauce. Beans were tender and creamy. Squash and mushrooms all came together with robust flavor. Def worth it. Does not need any meat at all to stand on its own. The chicken enchilado. Boneless thigh crispy fried. The meat has great flavor, no simple marinade here. A bouquet of bite sized Vegetable medley (purslane, cauliflower, fresh roasted corn, perfect carmelized Pearl onions, broccolini, roasted potatoes) with the most beautiful Chipotle sauce I've ever experienced. They won't share the recipe tho, this makes me sad. I did watch it get prepared but missed all the ingredients Being added. Its rich, floral, delicate, not overly Smokey or hot. I would put this sauce on everything. It makes me want to try every one of their sauces, which I plan to do soon. Yes. It's pricey. But. Every piece of produce was fresh and crisp . Every single Berry on my dessert was perfect, not a hint of age, no black, no mush, no mold and all sweet. You might wanna say it's luck, but not dead winter. Plus they're open 7 days a week.

A welcome addition to a neighborhood which has very few authentic Mexican places. Aleli is more on the "contemporary Mexican" side of things, a place you'd go for a beautifully prepared unique entrée that probably took all day to make, as there's so much complexity in the sauces. Chicken enchiladas were amazing — loved the pipián verde and toasted sesame seeds on top — it has all the components of a well balanced dish (salt, fat, acid, heat). My partner had the short rib, very different flavor but equally as good. Service was attentive and even brought over some additional napkins before we asked. Will be going back!
Modern Mexican food with authentic spices that are hard to come across, nice portions and the quality of ingredients are great

This will be the go to Mexican place of the neighborhood in no time. Beautiful, minimal decoration, everything is new. I love how simple their menu is. We tried the guacamole and a few of the tacos. My girlfriend and I both loved the steak ones. And of course I had to drink a Tamarind Jarrito.. so good! To finish, we ordered the coconut flan. Incredible. The prices are not bad at all. Service was also very friendly and courteous. Thanks for an amazing dinner, we'll be back soon!
